# Bold text labels

Text labels that name a field (form labels, read-only field captions like **Schedule**, **Last run**, **Status**, dialog section labels) should be **bold** so they read clearly as labels rather than values.

## Rule

When rendering a label for a field or labeled value group, set `fontWeight` to **700** (or `bold`) in `sx`. Keep the value text at normal weight unless it has another role (e.g. emphasized title).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — label and value weight look the same
<Typography variant="caption" color="text.secondary">
  Schedule
</Typography>
<Typography variant="body2">{scheduleCode}</Typography>

// ✅ GOOD
<Typography variant="caption" color="text.secondary" sx={{ fontWeight: 700 }}>
  Schedule
</Typography>
<Typography variant="body2">{scheduleCode}</Typography>
```

## Applies to

- Read-only field labels on admin/detail cards
- Form field helper labels that act as the field name (when not using MUI `InputLabel` / `FormLabel`, which already convey hierarchy)
- Section or dialog labels that identify the meaning of nearby content

## Does not apply to

- Body copy, descriptions, helper hints that are not field names
- Button text, chip labels, navigation items
- Page titles / headings (use heading variants instead)
